The paper deals with the problem of counting induced subgraphs in a graph that satisfy a given property, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses tools from computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG) to prove hardness results. The use of graph motifs and simplicial complexes suggests a connection to algebraic topology and combinatorial geometry (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of counting subgraphs, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
